<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to NE Brazil, growing in scrub around rock outcrops principally on or near the Serra de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Carajás">Carajas</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
BRAZIL. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: Serra de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Carajás">Carajas</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M.G. Silva &amp; R. Bahia</emphasis>
2911 MG, FTG, RB); ibid., Serra Norte, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. Cavalcante &amp; M. Silva</emphasis>
2651 (MG); ibid., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C.R. Sperling et al.</emphasis>
5584 (MO); ibid., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H.C. de Lima</emphasis>
7099 (RB); Mun. Itaituba, estrada 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Santarém-Cuiabá">Santarem-Cuiaba</normalizedToken>
, BR 163, km 816, Serra do Cachimbo, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I.L. Amaral et al.</emphasis>
1028, (FTG). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Tocantins</emphasis>
: Mun. Tocantinopolis, Ribeiro do Corrego, along Belem-Brasilia highway, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. Plowman et al.</emphasis>
9250 (MG, FTG).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes</emphasis>
. The erect habit, oblong, shortly petiolate leaves combined with the hypocrateriform vermilion corolla make this species very distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A hybrid between this species and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marabaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea marabaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded and illustrated by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Simão-Bianchini">Simao-Bianchini</normalizedToken>
et al. (2016: 1311).
</paragraph>
